{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC23","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Beyond scroll views","role":"sampleCode"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (14 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10159","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10159-beyond-scroll-views"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"About ScrollView","anchor":"About-ScrollView","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/scrollview"},{"type":"text","text":" is an important block that lets you show everything that won’t fit on screen. Scroll views have axes that define the directions in which they’re scrollable. Scroll views have content, when it exceeds the size of the ScrollView, some of that content will be clipped. Scroll views ensure that the content is placed within the safe area by resolving the safe area into margins outsetting its content. A ScrollView evaluates its content either eagerly or lazily by using a lazy stack."}]},{"text":"Margins and safe area","anchor":"Margins-and-safe-area","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Content is clipped when scrolling if you add padding to the ScrollView"}]},{"code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","  LazyHStack(spacing: Spacing) {","    ForEach(palettes) { palette in","      HeroView(palette: palette)","    }","  }","}",".padding(.horizontal, hMargin)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"New ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/safeareapadding(_:)-5lh9p","isActive":true},{"text":" adds padding to the safe area","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","  LazyHStack(spacing: Spacing) {","    ForEach(palettes) { palette in","      HeroView(palette: palette)","    }","  }","}",".safeAreaPadding(.horizontal, hMargin)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC23-10159-margins","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Different insets for different kinds of content","anchor":"Different-insets-for-different-kinds-of-content","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inset the content of the ScrollView separately from the scroll indicators with ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/contentmargins(_:_:for:)-1lt8b"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView {","  \/\/ content","｝",".contentMargins(","  .vertical, 50.0,","  for: .scrollContent",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inset the indicators separately from the content"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView {","  \/\/ content","｝",".contentMargins(","  .vertical, 50.0,","  for: .scrollIndicators",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"So, for the previous example, it is better to use the "},{"isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"contentMargins","type":"codeVoice"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/contentmargins(_:_:for:)-1lt8b","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"contentMargins"},{"type":"text","text":" API"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","  LazyHStack(spacing: Spacing) {","    ForEach(palettes) { palette in","      HeroView(palette: palette)","    }","  }","}",".contentMargins(","  .horizontal, hMargin,","  for: .scrollContent",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Target content offset","anchor":"Target-content-offset","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control what content offset the ScrollView will scroll to once someone lifts their finger with the new "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltargetbehavior(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Paging","anchor":"Paging","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Swipes one page at a time","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","  LazyHStack(spacing: Spacing) {","    ForEach(palettes) { palette in","      HeroView(palette: palette)","    }","  }","}",".contentMargins(.horizontal, hMargin)",".scrollTargetBehavior(.paging)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"View aligned","anchor":"View-aligned","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When aligned to individual views, ScrollView needs to know which views it should consider for alignment. Use the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltargetlayout(isenabled:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" modifier to have each view in the stack be considered a scroll target."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","  LazyHStack(spacing: Spacing) {","    ForEach(palettes) { palette in","      HeroView(palette: palette)","    }","  }","  .scrollTargetLayout()","}",".contentMargins(.horizontal, hMargin)",".scrollTargetBehavior(.viewAligned)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"One more API to mark individual views as targets with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"scrollTarget"},{"text":" modifier was mentioned during the session, but in fact it wasn’t released.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"⚠️ Note"},{"type":"heading","text":"Custom alignment","anchor":"Custom-alignment","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Conform to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/scrolltargetbehavior","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct GalleryScrollTargetBehavior: ScrollTargetBehavior {","  func updateTarget(_ target: inout ScrollTarget, context: TargetContext) {","    if target.rect.minY < (context.containerSize.height \/ 3.0),","      context.velocity.dy < 0.0 ","    {","      target.rect.origin.y = 0.0","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"View size based on container size","anchor":"View-size-based-on-container-size","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use new "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/containerrelativeframe(_:count:span:spacing:alignment:)"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier to set view size based on it’s container size."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Witdh of a container","anchor":"Witdh-of-a-container","level":4},{"code":["HeroColorStack(palette: palette)","  .frame(height: 250.0)","  .containerRelativeFrame(.horizontal)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC23-10159-container_1"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Grid like layout","anchor":"Grid-like-layout","level":4},{"code":["HeroColorStack(palette: palette)","  .frame(height: 250.0)","  .containerRelativeFrame(","    .horizontal,","    count: 2,","    spacing: 10.0","  )"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC23-10159-container_2"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Conditionalize the count based on the "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/environmentvalues\/horizontalsizeclass","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" - two columns on ipad and one column on iphone"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Environment(\\.horizontalSizeClass) private var sizeClass","","HeroColorStack(palette: palette)","  .frame(height: 250.0)","  .containerRelativeFrame(","    .horizontal,","    count: sizeClass == .regular ? 2 : 1,","    spacing: 10.0","  )"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/aspectratio(_:contentmode:)-771ow","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to have a height relative to the width, instead of hardcoding a fixed height"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Environment(\\.horizontalSizeClass) private var sizeClass","","HeroColorStack(palette: palette)","  .aspectRatio(16.0\/9.0, contentMode: .fit)","  .containerRelativeFrame(","    .horizontal,","    count: sizeClass == .regular ? 2 : 1,","    spacing: 10.0","  )"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Scroll indicators","anchor":"Scroll-indicators","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrollindicators(_:axes:)"},{"text":" hides the indicators on touch devices or when using more flexible input devices, like trackpads on Mac, but to allow the indicators to show when a mouse is connected.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"scrollIndicators(.never)"}],"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrollindicators(_:axes:)","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"scrollIndicators(.never)"},{"text":" to always hide the indicators regardless of input device.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Change position","anchor":"Change-position","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Change scroll position programmatically wth ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrollposition(id:anchor:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" modifier","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@State private var mainID: Palette.ID? = nil","","VStack {","  GallerySectionHeader(mainID: $mainID)","  ScrollView(.horizontal) { ... }","    .scrollPosition(id: $mainID)","}","","\/\/ in GallerySectionHeader","VStack {","  GalleryHeaderText()","  .overlay {","    GalleryPaddle(edge: .leading) {","      \/\/ When the binding is written to, the ScrollView will scroll to the view with that ID","      mainID = previousID()","    }","    \/\/ ...","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Scroll position modifier also uses the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltargetlayout(isenabled:)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"code":"scrollTargetLayout","type":"codeVoice"}],"overridingTitle":"scrollTargetLayout"},{"text":" modifier to know which views to consider for querying their identity values","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Read position","anchor":"Read-position","level":4},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"scrollPosition","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrollposition(id:anchor:)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"scrollPosition"}]},{"type":"text","text":" also allows to know the identity of the view currently scrolled"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ in GallerySectionHeader","@Binding var mainID: Palette.ID?","","VStack {","  GalleryHeaderText()","  \/\/ Header view has text that shows the value of the hero image currently scrolled","  \/\/ When the most leading view changes, the binding automatically updates","  GallerySubheaderText(id: mainID)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Scroll transitions","anchor":"Scroll-transitions","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Scale view down in size when it gets near the edges of the ScrollView wirh ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltransition(_:axis:transition:)","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HeroView(palette: palette)","  .scrollTransition(axis: .horizontal) { content, phase in","    content","      .scaleEffect(","        x: phase.isIdentity ? 1.0 : 0.80,","        y: phase.isIdentity ? 1.0 : 0.80","      )","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rotation or offset can be custimized as well. But not all view modifiers can be used inside of a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"scrollTransition","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltransition(_:axis:transition:)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"scrollTransition"}]},{"type":"text","text":". For example, customizing the font is not supported. Anything that will change the overall content size of the ScrollView cannot be used within a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"scrollTransition","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/view\/scrolltransition(_:axis:transition:)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"scrollTransition"}]},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HeroView(palette: palette)","  .scrollTransition(axis: .horizontal) {","    content, phase in","    content","      .scaleEffect(","        x: phase.isIdentity ? 1.0 : 0.80,","        y: phase.isIdentity ? 1.0 : 0.80","      )","      .rotationEffect(","        .degrees(phase.isIdentity ? 0.0 : 90.0)","      )","      .offset(","      